summary: The Human Papillomavirus (HPV) Testing Market is projected to grow from USD 1.52 billion in 2024 to USD 3.62 billion by 2033, at a 10.11% CAGR from 2025. This growth is fueled by increased cervical cancer awareness, robust screening programs, and advancements in diagnostic technologies. HPV, a significant sexually transmitted infection, plays a critical role in cervical and other cancers, highlighting the importance of early detection through testing.
